## Plan Summary

**Root Cause:** Classic off-by-one error in `src/utils.ts`, line 7.

The loop condition in `processItems()` reads:
```ts
for (let i = 0; i < items.length - 1; i++)
//                         ^^^^^^^^^ subtracting 1 skips the last element
```

This makes the loop stop at index `length - 2`, never touching the final item.

**The Fix — one character change:**
```ts
// Before (buggy)
for (let i = 0; i < items.length - 1; i++) {

// After (fixed)
for (let i = 0; i < items.length; i++) {
```

**Impact:** 3 of the 6 existing tests are currently failing because of this bug. After the fix, all 6 should pass.

Shall I go ahead and apply this fix?

